                <h2>Heavy Equipment Operator</h2>
                <p><strong>Job Description:</strong> Heavy equipment operators operate large machinery like bulldozers, excavators, and cranes on construction sites. They are responsible for digging, lifting, and moving heavy materials.</p>
                <p><strong>Salary:</strong> 25 per hour.</p>
                <p><strong>Working Conditions:</strong> Operators work outdoors and inside heavy equipment cabs, following safety protocols. They handle powerful machinery and work in various weather conditions.</p>
                <p><strong>Working Hours:</strong> Full-time positions with regular hours, but extended hours may be necessary to meet project deadlines.</p>
                <p><strong>Ease of Job:</strong> The job requires specialized training to operate heavy equipment safely and efficiently.</p>
                <p><strong>Job Location:</strong> Construction sites and industrial areas within the region.</p>
            </div>
            
            <button class="apply-button" onclick="openGoogleForm()">Apply Now</button>
        </div>
